vim-mason
=========

Vim syntax file for Mason (Perl embedded in HTML) based on the version of Andrew Smith
from http://www.masonhq.com/editors/mason.vim


## Installation

If you don't have a preferred installation method, you can use [vundle]() to install
this script. If you have vundle installed, just paste following to your .vimrc file:

  Bundle 'aming/vim-mason'

You can also just put all the files and directory to your vim directory.

